Objective and subjective security and safety of adventure activities. Physical security - environment, equipment and activities. Psychological security. Emergency in critical situations. Make acquaintance with the Estonian Rescue Team and its functions. Risk analysis. TeamworkObjectives/eesmärkid:  The main goal is to introduce the physical and safety aspects of the adventure activities, to prevent risk and use first aid; To give an overview of adventure activities in nature- social- and cultural environment, also knowledges of group process; to introduce search and resque simulations in adventure and life.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student is able to:
to give first aid to the journey and adventure trails,
to organize the search and rescue operations during adventure simulation in different seasons, 
to assess and analyze the activities of the group, to to recognize different phases of the group development. 
Knows basic how to use equipment and keep the adventure.
